Sanchez Says Labor Concerns Won’t Stop Two Free Trade Agreements

-- B y   E r i c   M a r t i n
-- 
2011-03-16T14:47:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-15/mcconnell-says-republicans-to-stop-nominees-on-trade-deals-2-.html
Concerns that Colombia and  Panama 
haven’t done enough to protect organized labor leaders don’t
threaten free-trade agreements with those nations, said
Francisco Sanchez, under secretary of Commerce for international
trade.  “We’re confident we’ll have the issues resolved this
year,” Sanchez said today in  Washington  at a hearing of the
House Energy and Commerce subcommittee on commerce,
manufacturing and trade.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Martin in Washington at 
 emartin21@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Larry Liebert at 
 lliebert@bloomberg.net  